<sect1 id="elem_target" xreflabel="Element: &lt;target&gt;">
<?dbhtml filename="elem_target.html" dir="alfs_dtd"?>
<title>Element: &lt;target&gt;</title>

<sect2>
<title>Syntax</title>

<synopsis>
&lt;!ELEMENT target         (#PCDATA)&gt;
</synopsis>

<para>This element occurs in the element&nbsp;:&nbsp;&nbsp;
<xref linkend="elem_link"/>
</para>

</sect2>

<sect2>
<title>Description</title>

<para>The element <filename>target</filename> describes a target of a link
operation.</para>

</sect2>

<sect2>
<title>Examples</title>

<userinput><screen>&lt;link&gt;
	&lt;target&gt;share/man&lt;/target&gt;
	&lt;target&gt;share/doc&lt;/target&gt;
	&lt;target&gt;share/info&lt;/target&gt;
	&lt;name&gt;/usr/local&lt;/name&gt;
&lt;/link&gt;</screen></userinput>

<para>The equivalent bash script is&nbsp;:</para>

<userinput><screen>echo 'Linking  share/man share/doc share/info into /usr/local'
<command>ln -s  share/man share/doc share/info /usr/local</command></screen></userinput>

</sect2>

</sect1>
